  "networkHubPage": {
    "title": "Network Hub",
    "intro": "Empowering organizations to build agile, intelligent, and future-ready networks that connect people, data, and applications ‚Äî with unmatched performance and reliability.",
    "introParagraph": "The Network Hub empowers organizations to design, build, and operate high performance infrastructures that connect people, applications, and data with speed and reliability. We deliver enterprise-grade LAN, WAN, and data center architectures that integrate automation, visibility, and cloud-ready scalability at every layer. By leveraging the latest Software-Defined Networking (SDN) frameworks, we enable centralized control, faster provisioning, and consistent policy across physical and virtual domains. Our engineers blend modern SDN fabrics with proven routing and switching design to create networks that are adaptive, secure, and future-proof. From enterprise campuses to global hybrid clouds, Stackhubs networks are built to perform intelligently, efficiently, and without compromise. ",
    "introTitle": "Intro Paragraph",
    "cta": "Talk to our experts",
    "whatWeDeliverTitle": "What We Deliver",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Enterprise Networks & Smart Campus Solutions",
        "desc": "We design and deploy enterprise network infrastructures that combine wired, wireless, and identity-driven access into a unified fabric. Our solutions deliver high availability, scalable segmentation, and deep visibility across all user and device types. We implement Cisco Software-Defined Access (SDA) to bring automation and policy consistency to campus environments, and extend it through multisite capabilities for unified management across distributed locations. The result is a secure, intelligent enterprise network that provides seamless mobility, zero-touch provisioning, and centralized operations across every site. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Data Center & Cloud Fabric",
        "desc": "Modern workloads demand agility, security, and automation and our data center networking delivers all three. We design spine-leaf fabrics with EVPN/VXLAN overlays, delivering scalability, multi-tenant segmentation, and low-latency performance. Our data center framework integrates Cisco Application Centric Infrastructure (ACI) for policy-based automation, including Multipod and Multisite designs managed through NDO and analyzed with NDI for end-to-end visibility. We connect on-premises data centers with hybrid and multi-cloud environments seamlessly, ensuring consistent policy enforcement and optimized traffic flow wherever your workloads run. "
      },
      {
        "title": "SD-WAN & Multi-Site Connectivity",
        "desc": "We modernize WAN architectures with intelligent, application-aware routing and simplified management. Our SD-WAN solutions enhance cloud performance, security, and cost efficiency across multiple carriers and geographies. We deliver Cisco SD-WAN for enterprise-scale control and segmentation, Meraki SD-WAN for agile, cloud-managed simplicity, and integrate VMware VeloCloud and Fortinet SD-WAN where edge flexibility or unified security is key. Every deployment is engineered for high availability, optimized user experience, and centralized visibility through advanced analytics and orchestration. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Network Automation & Orchestration",
        "desc": "Automation drives speed, accuracy, and operational excellence. We build automation frameworks that standardize configuration, accelerate rollout, and ensure compliance using model-driven templates, APIs, and orchestration tools. Our SDN-ready automation workflows cover provisioning, policy management, performance assurance, and lifecycle operations reducing human error and improving reliability. With Stackhubs automation, your network becomes truly intent-based: responsive, self-optimizing, and easy to scale. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Security Integration & Zero-Trust Alignment",
        "desc": "Every Stackhubs network is designed with built-in security. Our architectures integrate seamlessly with the InfoSec Hub, aligning advanced network segmentation, identity enforcement, and zero-trust principles from edge to core. We combine real-time visibility, encrypted traffic analytics, and automated response mechanisms to ensure continuous protection without performance trade-offs. The result: a unified ecosystem where networking and security operate as one. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Performance & Observability",
        "desc": "Visibility is the foundation of reliability. We embed telemetry, flow analytics, and AI-driven monitoring tools that track every packet and path in real time. Through continuous analysis and predictive insights, we identify bottlenecks, optimize routing, and fine-tune QoS policies to guarantee a consistent user experience. Our observability platforms integrate directly with your SDN controllers and performance systems keeping the network healthy, fast, and always aligned with business¬†priorities."
      }
    ],
    "ctaTitle": "Ready to Modernize Your Network?",
    "ctaSubtitle": "Discover how StackHubs can help you build a smarter, faster, and more secure digital foundation.",
    "ctaButton": "Talk to our experts"
  },
  "infoSecHubPage": {
    "title": "InfoSec Hub",
    "intro": "Building secure, resilient digital ecosystems across the MENA region.",
    "cta": "Talk to our experts",
    "introParagraph": "In an era of constant digital expansion, cybersecurity is no longer a reactive function ‚Äî it is a core component of business continuity and trust. The InfoSec Hub at Stackhubs delivers end-to-end security architecture, operations, and assurance services that protect critical assets across infrastructure, applications, and cloud environments. We help organizations establish governance frameworks, implement defense-in-depth strategies, and maintain operational resilience through continuous monitoring and proactive threat response. Our security practice integrates seamlessly with all other hubs, ensuring protection is embedded at every layer ‚Äî from connectivity and access to data and workloads. Through industry best practices, automation, and regional compliance alignment, we help clients in the MENA region achieve robust, auditable, and adaptive security postures built for today‚Äôs evolving threat landscape.",
    "whatWeDeliverTitle": "What We Deliver",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Cybersecurity Architecture & Governance",
        "desc": "We develop holistic security architectures that align with your business goals and regulatory requirements. Our experts map every control layer ‚Äî network, cloud, application, and identity ‚Äî into a unified policy framework built on Zero Trust, NIST, and ISO 27001 principles. We design governance models that clearly define responsibilities, escalation paths, and compliance metrics, ensuring your operations stay auditable and secure. Through this architecture, organizations gain clarity, consistency, and confidence across all security domains."
      },
      {
        "title": "Threat Detection & Incident Response (SOC / SOAR)",
        "desc": "Stackhubs builds and operates Security Operations Centers (SOC) that combine human expertise with AI-driven analytics. We deploy and fine-tune SIEM and SOAR platforms to detect anomalies, correlate logs, and automate containment or remediation within seconds. Our incident response playbooks integrate directly with network, cloud, and endpoint systems, ensuring coordinated action across all layers. This enables your teams to transition from reactive defense to proactive threat hunting ‚Äî minimizing impact and accelerating recovery. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Identity & Access Management (IAM / PAM)",
        "desc": "We help organizations secure digital identities through centralized authentication, authorization, and privilege control. Our implementations include Identity Governance (IGA), Single Sign-On (SSO), Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA), and Privileged Access Management (PAM) solutions. We integrate with existing directory services and cloud identity providers to maintain seamless access for users while enforcing strict least-privilege and just-in-time access models. The result is a consistent, traceable, and secure identity ecosystem across every platform and application."
      },
      {
        "title": "Network & Cloud Security",
        "desc": "We deliver unified security across on-premises, hybrid, and cloud environments to ensure consistent visibility and control. Our engineers design layered protection using Next-Generation Firewalls (NGFW), Intrusion Prevention Systems (IPS), and Web Application Firewalls (WAF) integrated with Cloud Security Posture Management (CSPM) and Workload Protection Platforms (CWPP). We secure cloud-native workloads, containers, and APIs while enforcing segmentation and encrypted traffic analytics across the network. Through tight integration with the Network Hub, we ensure that every connection, workload, and user operates within a protected, policy-driven framework. This holistic approach provides unified threat visibility and control from the data center to the public cloud. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Governance, Risk & Compliance (GRC)",
        "desc": "Our GRC practice ensures that cybersecurity is embedded within organizational governance, not treated as a separate function. We help enterprises in the Middle East and North Africa achieve regulatory alignment and maintain continuous compliance across national and sector-specific frameworks. Our consultants implement structured governance models, clear risk ownership, and measurable control maturity programs tailored to each client‚Äôs environment. We align with ISO 27001, NCA ECC (Saudi Arabia), DESC / ADQCC (UAE), and NTRA Cyber Framework (Egypt) while mapping them to global standards such as NIST and CIS. The team conducts risk assessments, control gap analyses, and policy audits, ensuring accountability from board level to technical operations. Through awareness programs and executive reporting, we build a culture of compliance that strengthens resilience and decision-making. The outcome is a transparent, auditable, and trusted cybersecurity posture that satisfies regulators and enhances business confidence."
      },
      {
        "title": "Penetration Testing & Assessment Services",
        "desc": "Our StackHubs red-team specialists conduct comprehensive penetration testing to identify vulnerabilities before attackers can exploit them. We perform network, web application, wireless, and social engineering assessments, simulating real-world attacks to validate your defenses. In addition, our vulnerability management programs prioritize and remediate risks based on exploitability and business impact. Each engagement concludes with a detailed technical and executive report outlining findings, remediation paths, and long-term hardening recommendations. These services provide both assurance and actionable insights to maintain a continuously improving defense posture."
      }
    ],
    "ctaTitle": "Ready to Secure Your Digital Future?",
    "ctaSubtitle": "Partner with Stackhubs InfoSec Hub to build resilient, compliant, and trusted infrastructures.",
    "ctaButton": "Talk to our experts"
  },
  "wirelessHubPage": {
    "title": "Wireless Hub",
    "intro": "Delivering the next generation of wireless connectivity for seamless mobility and performance.",
    "cta": "Talk to our experts",
    "introParagraph": "Wireless is no longer an add-on; it‚Äôs the primary access layer for users, devices, and IoT. Our Wireless Hub delivers end-to-end Wi-Fi architectures that combine RF design, security, and automation to achieve a consistent optimum experience at scale. We design for single strength, coverage, capacity, and engineering high-density environments with Wi-Fi 6/6E and ready for 7 using OFDMA and optimized channel plans in 2.4/5/6 GHz. Assurance is built in: active & predictive surveys, spectrum analysis, heatmaps, and continuous KPIs for latency, throughput, and roaming. Access is identity-driven with WPA3-Enterprise, 802.1X/EAP-TLS, NAC/Zero-Trust policy, and clean separation of production vs. guest traffic. We integrate wireless with the wider campus fabric (wired/SD-Access), deliver cloud-managed or controller-based operations, and support indoor, outdoor, and industrial sites. The outcome: fast, reliable, and cost-effective wireless that empowers mobility, VoIP/real-time apps, and large-scale IoT‚Äîanywhere.",
    "whatWeDeliverTitle": "What We Deliver",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "RF Strategy, Predictive Design & On-Site Validation",
        "desc": "We capture use-cases, device mix, concurrency, and SLAs, then translate them into an RF model (materials, AP placement, antenna patterns, channel widths, Tx power, data-rate thresholds). We use world-class tools like Ekahau to do our predictive design, produce heatmaps for coverage (RSSI/SNR), capacity, CCI/ACI, and 6-GHz viability, so deployment starts from a known-good baseline. We verify in the field with active/passive surveys, measuring real throughput, loss, jitter, roaming times, DHCP/DNS success, and retry rates. Spectrum analysis identifies non-Wi-Fi interferers (BLE, microwave, cameras, IoT), and we prescribe mitigations: clean channels, directional antennas, shielding, or relocation. Turn-up tuning covers cell size, power/channel plans, client steering, and sticky-client handling to hit target KPIs. Deliverables include updated heatmaps, survey files, spectrum captures, and an acceptance report mapped to your SLAs. "
      },
      {
        "title": "High-Density Performance Engineering (Wi-Fi 6/6E/7-ready)",
        "desc": "We design for crowded venues with OFDMA scheduling, MU-MIMO, BSS coloring, and precise cell sizing to maximize airtime efficiency. Client-steering and band-balancing policies keep the load even across 2.4/5/6 GHz while honoring device capabilities. End-to-end QoS ensures that voice, video, and real-time applications receive deterministic latency and jitter. Roaming is optimized using 802.11r/k/v, fast BSS transition, and minimized re-authentication penalties. We harden DHCP/DNS paths, prune broadcast/multicast traffic, and tune retry/CTS thresholds for enhanced reliability. Performance baselines and stress tests validate throughput per client profile under peak concurrency. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Secure Access & Segmentation (Prod / Guest)",
        "desc": "Identity-driven access with WPA3-Enterprise, 802.1X/EAP-TLS, and granular NAC policies enforces least-privilege by user/device posture. We implement per-user VLANs or group tags for micro-segmentation without SSID sprawl. Guest and contractor flows are isolated end-to-end with rate limits, time bounds, and audit trails. Certificate lifecycle (enrollment/renewal/revocation) integrates with MDM/Intune/JAMF for zero-touch onboarding. Rogue AP/WIPS policies detect and contain unauthorized radios safely. The wireless team also engages with the network team to ensure Network Policy sets are mirrored into the wired campus fabric for consistent enforcement. "
      },
      {
        "title": "IoT & Location Services",
        "desc": "Our wireless team integrates with the IoT hub team to build IoT profiles for scanners, sensors, cameras, AGVs‚Äîright power, rates, and security for low-power and high-density fleets. Onboarding options include DPSK, certificates, or MAC-based exceptions with tight network scopes. We deploy BLE/ULP grids and calibrate RTLS to accuracy targets for wayfinding and asset tracking. Northbound APIs stream location/events to CMMS/ERP/EMS platforms. IoT traffic is isolated with rate limits and anomaly alerts to protect business apps. Operational runbooks define lifecycle tasks: adds/moves, firmware, and security rotation. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Controllers, Cloud-Managed Ops & Automation",
        "desc": "Choose controller-based or cloud-managed WLAN; both deliver RRM, policy, and zero-touch provisioning. We standardize configs with templates and expose change workflows via APIs/GitOps for auditability. Automations cover adds/moves/changes, bulk firmware, and config drift detection with guardrails. Health telemetry streams to your NOC/SOC for correlation with wired, DHCP/DNS, and app layers. Role-based access and approval flows keep operations safe and fast. Scheduled maintenance windows use staged rollouts and rollback plans to minimize impact. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Assurance, KPIs & Continuous Optimization",
        "desc": "We operate to explicit targets: ‚â•95% coverage, ‚â•98% roaming success, <30 ms latency for critical apps, and throughput per persona. Dashboards track SNR, retries, MCS distribution, roaming times, DHCP/DNS success, and client experience. Synthetic tests validate paths to key apps and detect degradations before users do. Quarterly reviews compare trends, incidents, and changes against KPIs and propose tuning actions. Event correlation ties RF changes to ticket volumes and user satisfaction. Reports are executive-friendly with technical appendices for engineering follow-up. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Guest Access & Captive Portal Experience",
        "desc": "Branded portals with voucher/SMS/social/SSO and granular T&Cs. Walled-garden and bandwidth caps protect core services while keeping UX smooth. Full segmentation from production, with logging and abuse controls. Short-lived credentials, device limits, and sponsored guest workflows. Marketing/analytics hooks (optional) for visit patterns and dwell time. Operational playbooks define sponsor approval and exception handling. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Documentation, Handover & Support Models",
        "desc": "You receive as-built diagrams, RF plans, finals of heatmaps/surveys, inventory, and runbooks. Admin training covers troubleshooting flows, KPIs, and safe-change practices. We provide warranty/firmware matrices and lifecycle roadmaps. Support tiers: design-assist, escalation-only, or fully managed Wi-Fi with SLAs. Proactive reviews keep configs aligned with device trends and regulations. A single contact window coordinates vendors, carriers, and campus integrations."
      }
    ],
    "ctaTitle": "Ready to Empower Mobility?",
    "ctaSubtitle": "Partner with Stackhubs Wireless Hub to build next-gen wireless infrastructures.",
    "ctaButton": "Talk to our experts"
  },
  "aiHubPage": {
    "title": "AI Hub",
    "intro": "AI at StackHubs transforms data into real business impact ‚Äî from automation to prediction, designed with governance, security, and observability at its core.",
    "cta": "Talk to our experts",
    "introParagraph": "AI at StackHubs is built to deliver measurable outcomes ‚Äî not experiments. We design end-to-end pipelines from data acquisition to production MLOps with governance, observability, and security by default. Models run where they create the most value: on edge gateways for real-time control, or in cloud for scale and analytics. Every solution is integrated with your existing systems (ERP/CRM, SIEM, VMS, data lake) and instrumented for audit and ROI. We support multilingual use cases including Arabic/RTL, with human-in-the-loop review where accuracy and compliance matter. Lifecycle management covers drift detection, retraining, and safe rollback so AI stays reliable in production. The result is an AI capability that‚Äôs practical, maintainable, and aligned with business KPIs. ",
    "whatWeDeliverTitle": "What We Deliver",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Computer Vision",
        "desc": "Real-time analytics on cameras for counting, intrusion, direction, heatmaps, and access control across sites. Edge inference on gateways/NVRs with GPU acceleration; cloud aggregation for fleet analytics and model updates. Pre/post-processing for occlusion, lighting, and privacy masks with configurable retention policies. Integrations to VMS/ACS/SIEM trigger alerts, door actions, or tickets in ITSM automatically. Multi-camera tracking and re-ID link events across entrances, corridors, and zones for full journey context. MLOps pipelines handle dataset curation, accuracy benchmarks, A/B deployments, and continuous improvement. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Document Intelligence (OCR + Forms + RPA)",
        "desc": "Layout-aware OCR extracts structured data from invoices, IDs, POs, delivery notes, and contracts with field validation. Entity capture (names, dates, totals, line items) with confidence scores and exception queues for human-in-the-loop. Arabic and bilingual documents supported (RTL, stamps, seals, and handwriting variants where feasible). Business rules and anti-fraud checks (duplicates, vendor mismatches, tax/IBAN validation) before posting. RPA workflows post directly into ERP/CRM, attach evidence, and update approval status automatically. Dashboards track STP rate, turnaround time, and accuracy to keep processes auditable and scalable. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Anomaly Detection & Predictive Maintenance",
        "desc": "Time-series and streaming analytics learn each asset/site‚Äôs normal to catch outliers early. Applies to networks, IoT fleets, machines, and fraud signals with unsupervised and hybrid models. Root-cause hints correlate sensors, logs, and events to cut MTTD/MTTR and prevent repeat failures. Health scores and remaining-useful-life (RUL) estimates drive proactive work orders in CMMS/ERP. Edge agents buffer during outages and sync summaries to the cloud for global insight and governance. Drift monitoring, retraining windows, and blue/green rollouts keep models accurate in production. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Speech & Conversational AI",
        "desc": "Live transcription, summaries, and sentiment for calls and meetings in Arabic and English. Voicebots/chatbots handle routine requests with guardrails, handoff to agents, and full conversation history. RAG-based assistants connect to your knowledge bases and ticketing to answer with cited sources. Acoustic enhancements reduce noise/overlap; diarization separates speakers for clean analytics. Supervision tools review accuracy, bias, and leakage risks with redaction and retention controls. Contact-center KPIs (AHT, FCR, CSAT) improve through intent routing, coaching cues, and after-call summaries. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Forecasting & Decision Optimization",
        "desc": "Statistical and ML forecasting for demand, inventory, staffing, capacity, and energy consumption. Scenario planning simulates shocks, seasonality, and promotions with confidence intervals and alerts. Optimization engines schedule workforce, routes, or production under real-world constraints and SLAs. What-if tools expose trade-offs (service vs. cost vs. risk) with executive-level dashboards. Tight integration with ERP/MES/SCM ensures recommended actions flow into operations automatically. Continuous backtesting and champion‚Äìchallenger deployment keep models honest and improving."
      }
    ],
    "ctaTitle": "Ready to Accelerate with AI?",
    "ctaSubtitle": "Partner with StackHubs AI Hub to bring intelligence and automation into every layer of your business.",
    "ctaButton": "Talk to our experts"
  },
  "iotHubPage": {
    "title": "IoT Hub",
    "intro": "The IoT Hub connects assets, environments, and people through secure devices, resilient connectivity, and real-time data pipelines.",
    "introParagraph": "We design end-to-end architectures‚Äîfrom sensor selection and edge gateways to cloud platforms and integrations with ERP/CMMS/SCADA. Connectivity is engineered for each use case: Wi-Fi/6E for campus, BLE for tagging, LPWAN for low-power fleets, and 4G/5G/private-LTE for mobility and remote sites. Security is built in with device identity, least-privilege network access, encrypted transport, and continuous posture monitoring. Data moves through streaming and digital-twin models so operations, maintenance, and business apps can act in seconds, not hours. The result is an industrial-grade IoT foundation that scales safely, reduces downtime, and unlocks new automation and visibility across your sites.",
    "cta": "Talk to our experts",
    "whatWeDeliverTitle": "What We Deliver",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Industrial IoT & Smart Facilities",
        "desc": "We instrument production lines, utilities, and buildings with sensors for condition, energy, safety, and environment. Edge gateways normalize field protocols (Modbus, BACnet, OPC-UA, CAN) and bridge to IT networks securely. We integrate with PLC/SCADA/BMS to stream alarms and KPIs while respecting control-system boundaries. Device identity, certificates, and secure boot protect endpoints from spoofing and tampering. Digital-twin models mirror assets to track state, utilization, and maintenance history. Outcomes: fewer site visits, faster fault isolation, and a single operational view across facilities. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Connectivity & Device Management",
        "desc": "Right-sized connectivity per fleet: Wi-Fi/6E, BLE/RTLS, LoRa/LPWAN, 4G/5G/private-LTE, and secure backhaul. We implement onboarding at scale (DPSK/certificates), profile policies, and micro-segmentation for IoT traffic. Automated lifecycle: enrollment, provisioning, firmware/OTA, key rotation, and decommissioning with audit trails. Health telemetry and anomaly rules detect chatty or misbehaving devices before they impact apps. Gateway high-availability and offline buffering keep data flowing during WAN outages. Unified consoles show inventory, status, compliance, and performance by site and device type. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Data Platform & Integration",
        "desc": "Streaming pipelines ingest time-series, events, and video into a governed lakehouse with role-based access. We build APIs and connectors to ERP/CMMS/EMS and analytics tools so insights drive work orders and actions. Schema, retention, and PII policies keep data useful and compliant across teams. Dashboards surface live KPIs‚ÄîOEE/energy/condition‚Äîplus drill-downs to device level. Rules engines trigger alerts, ticketing, and workflows with throttling and deduplication. Optional document intelligence and computer vision modules enrich events with OCR or camera analytics. "
      },
      {
        "title": "Analytics, Alerts & Predictive Maintenance",
