      "summary": "Ghazala Bay Hotel, a luxury resort on Egypt‚Äôs North Coast, partnered with Stackhubs to modernize its entire wireless network using Aruba Wi-Fi 6 technology. The engagement replaced an aging system with a new, high-performance wireless infrastructure covering 400+ guest rooms, public areas, and outdoor zones. The project included complete RF surveys, heatmaps, and design validation with Ekahau, LAN switch upgrades, and secure segmentation for guest and staff networks. Stackhubs completed the rollout within 2 months and now provides managed wireless service and monitoring to ensure consistent connectivity for guests and operations.",
